{
  "doc_id": "34932",
  "text": "In our research, age was an independent prognostic factor for ACHBLF, which was consistent with the previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Xie et al. [CITATION_3] found that the mortality of HBV related liver failure increased markedly with increasing age ≥ 35 years in males and ≥ 55 years in females. In patients with chronic liver disease, liver function deteriorates with age and the regenerative capacity of the liver declines [28] . The older patients are more easily combined with complications because of low immunity.",
